Durban - Poor weather conditions forced rescue teams to abandon their search for a young boy, who went missing while swimming at Blythedale beach on Monday. 
This morning, IPSS Medical Rescue teamed up with KwaDukuza lifeguards and officers from the SAPS Search and Rescue Unit to search for the 16-year-old Gledhow resident. 

On Monday, the boy is believed to have gotten swept away out to sea. 
IPSS Medical Rescue spokesperson, Paul Herbst, said several vessels were launched, covering the northern and southern sides of the point of entry. 

“Four vessels were launched this morning and beach patrols were also conducted with negative results,” he said. 


 







